{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6aaee1ba-708a-4e8a-b5b1-a1979116332d","content":"TUnit uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively. Filter by class with `--treenode-filter`:\n\n```bash\ndotnet run --project TestProject.csproj -- --treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests/*\"\n```\n\nThe treenode filter pattern is `/Assembly/Namespace/Class/Test` — the wildcards match any assembly and namespace, then select only `SmsNotificationTests`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a11c6fb3-8d67-463b-b9d6-f654921eca59","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"This is a TUnit project. TUnit uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) as its native runner. To filter by class, I need to use the appropriate filter syntax.\n\nTUnit uses `--treenode-filter` for filtering. To filter by class name:\n\n```\ndotnet run --project TestProject.csproj -- --treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests/*\"\n```\n\nOr with `dotnet test` using VSTest filter:\n\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"ClassName~SmsNotificationTests\"\n```\n\nActually, TUnit v0.6.x uses MTP natively. The recommended way is:\n\n\nThe treenode filter format follows the pattern `/AssemblyName/Namespace/ClassName/TestName`, so I can filter by class using either the wildcard pattern `/*/*/SmsNotificationTests/*` or the more specific `/TestProject/Contoso.Notifications.Tests/SmsNotificationTests/*`.","outputTokens":362},"id":"29ec072b-5576-420a-be2c-a31745b8cf91","timestamp":"2026-04-03T02:18:31.584Z","parentId":"e027a3e8-b1c4-46f9-a19f-894b2eab556b"}
